Researchers said that this new study tested the impact of cash on global mortality for the first time. From 2000 to 2019, they collected information about 29 African African countries, one North African country, four Asia -Pacific countries, and three Latin America and Caribbean countries.

They recorded more than 4 million adults and nearly 3 million children, and about 300,000 people died during the study. The recipient will get a cash of 6%to 13%per capita income of specific countries, usually less than $ 100.

